1274年托马斯·阿奎那病逝，死后尸体被教徒分食。<ref>{{cite news |title=The Autumn of the Middle Ages |url=https://book.douban.com/subject/1471331/ |accessdate=1950-10-29 |agency=豆瓣读书 |date=2020-11-16 |archive-date=2020-08-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200805113315/https://book.douban.com/subject/1471331/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

在1315年-1317年的欧洲大饥荒，因缺少基本储粮，受灾荒的欧洲各国都出现了大量人相食事件，其中有大量婴幼儿被吃掉。.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Pennell |first1=C.R. |title=Cannibalism in Early Modern North Africa |journal=British Journal of Middle Eastern Studies |date=1991 |volume=18 |issue=2 |pages=169–185 |jstor=196038 |doi=10.1080/13530199108705536 }}</ref>

==殖民时代==

西班牙探险家阿尔瓦·努涅斯·卡韦萨·德·巴卡在一次航海中，因遭到沉船事故，与幸存船员分食死去船员的遗骸，<ref>W. W. Newcomb, Jr.,''The Indians of Texas: From Prehistoric to Modern Times'' Austin: University of Texas Press, 1999, p. 77</ref>

1514年7月21日，被俘的匈牙利叛军领袖[[György_Dózsa|György Dózsa]]被残酷的酷刑虐待。在他受刑的时候，行刑者撕开他的肉后将他的肉分给士兵和平民。<ref>{{cite book|last=Barabási|first=Albert-László|title=Bursts|edition=First|year=2010|publisher=[[Penguin_Group|Penguin Group]]|location=New York, United States|isbn=978-0-525-95160-5|pages=[https://archive.org/details/burstshiddenpatt00bara/page/263 263–266]|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/burstshiddenpatt00bara/page/263}}</ref>

1612年波兰军队入侵莫斯科时期也有大量人相食事件发生。<ref>К. Валишевский. «Смутное время». М., 1993. С. 293–294. {{ISBN|5-8498-0037-9}}</ref>
<ref>W Bruce Lincoln, ''The Conquest of a Continent'', p. 65, citing Akheograficheskaya Kommissia,''Dopolneniia k Aktam Istoricheskim'', St Petersburg 1846–72, III, document 12, pp. 52–60.</ref>

英格兰女海盗船长夏洛特·德·贝里（Charlotte de Berry）也有过食人行为，她在几次海难中都是通过分食同伴的遗骸而幸存下来。<ref name="Zuidhoek">{{cite book|last1=Zuidhoek|first1=Arne|title=A-Z Pirate Encyclopedia: Deprived of God & Country|date=2015|publisher=Uitgeverij Julius de Goede BV|location=Utrecht|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=g4euAQAACAAJ|accessdate=29 September 2017|language=en|archive-date=2020-06-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200612125535/https://books.google.com/books?id=g4euAQAACAAJ|dead-url=no}}</ref>

1672年8月20日，一个基督教暴徒私刑处死了[[Johan_de_Witt|Johan de Witt]]并且吃掉了他的遗骸<ref>{{aut|Kok, J.}} (1794) ''Vaderlandsch woordenboek; oorspronkelijk verzameld door Jacobus Kok. Deel 32'', p. 352; {{aut|Veeghens, D.}} (1884) ''Historische studien: Uitg. door J.D. Veegens. Eerste Deel'', p. 48; the first name of Verhoeff was Hendrick according to {{aut|Fruin, R.}} (1901) ''Robert Fruin's verspreide geschriften'', p. 374, note 2</ref>

苏格兰的詹姆斯·道格拉斯，昆士伯里第三侯爵（James Douglas, 3rd Marquess of Queensberry）因为食人行为被指控。<ref>[https://archive.org/stream/ahistoryhousedo00lindgoog#page/n356/mode/2up Maxwell vol ii, p284]</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.scottish-places.info/people/famousfirst651.html | title=James Douglas (Earl of Drumlanrig) | accessdate=2006-09-13 | publisher=The Gazetteer for Scotland | archive-date=2021-02-17 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210217104022/https://www.scottish-places.info/people/famousfirst651.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>

彼得·斯顿普（Peter Stumpp）因犯下食人罪被指控<ref>Orenstein, Catherine (2002) ''Little Red Riding Hood Uncloaked: Sex, Morality, and the Evolution of a Fairy Tale''. New York: Basic Books. p. 91, {{ISBN|0-465-04125-6}}</ref> 

卢克斯堡号在1727年发生了海难，幸存者在大西洋中部的一艘小船上发生了食人事件。<ref name="NMM">{{cite web|url=http://www.nmm.ac.uk/collections/explore/object.cfm?ID=BHC2389|title=The ''Luxborough Galley'' on fire, 25 June 1727 (BHC2389)|work=Paintings: description|publisher=[[National_Maritime_Museum|National Maritime Museum]]|accessdate=17 December 2010|archive-date=2011-08-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110828064336/http://www.nmm.ac.uk/collections/explore/object.cfm?ID=BHC2389|dead-url=no}}</ref>

富蘭克林於1818年首次進入北極地區，被它深深吸引。1819年至1822年間，富蘭克林帶領包括他在內共20人的隊伍在[[加拿大|加拿大]]西北地區沿[[科珀曼河|科珀曼河]]進行陸上探險，結果有11人中途喪生，當中大多數死於飢餓，其餘生還者曾被迫進食[[地衣|地衣]]維生，甚至試圖吃掉皮靴充飢，但最终因口粮用光，开始分食同伴的遗体。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rmg.co.uk/discover/explore/john-franklin%E2%80%99s-early-north-west-passage-expeditions-1819%E2%80%9327 |title=Topic: John Franklin’s early North-West Passage expeditions 1819–27 |accessdate=2016-05-27 |archive-date=2016-06-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160617010810/http://www.rmg.co.uk/discover/explore/john-franklin%E2%80%99s-early-north-west-passage-expeditions-1819%E2%80%9327 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==近代==
托马斯·杰弗里斯（Thomas Jeffries）是一位英格兰罪犯，被指控有食人行为。<ref>''Colonial Times'', 6 January 1826</ref><ref>''Hobart Town Gazette'', 29 April 1826</ref>

在爱尔兰大饥荒时期，也有大量人相食事件发生。<ref>{{cite news |title=An Intellectual History of Cannibalism |url=https://press.princeton.edu/books/paperback/9780691152196/an-intellectual-history-of-cannibalism |accessdate=1950-10-29 |agency=Philosophy |date=2020-11-16 |archive-date=2020-12-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201201151217/https://press.princeton.edu/books/paperback/9780691152196/an-intellectual-history-of-cannibalism |dead-url=no }}</ref>

著名的开膛手杰克也有食人行为。<ref name="mail">{{cite news|last1=Edwards|first1=Russell|title=Jack the Ripper unmasked|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2746321/Jack-Ripper-unmasked-How-amateur-sleuth-used-DNA-breakthrough-identify-Britains-notorious-criminal-126-years-string-terrible-murders.html|accessdate=2014年9月7日|work=Daily Mail|archive-date=2014年9月8日|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140908060726/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2746321/Jack-Ripper-unmasked-How-amateur-sleuth-used-DNA-breakthrough-identify-Britains-notorious-criminal-126-years-string-terrible-murders.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="independent">{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/science/has-jack-the-rippers-identity-really-been-revealed-using-dna-evidence-9717036.html|title=Has Jack the Ripper's identity really been revealed using DNA evidence?|date=2014年9月7日|work=[[獨立報|獨立報]]|accessdate=2021年1月5日|archive-date=2020年7月12日|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200712100659/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/science/has-jack-the-rippers-identity-really-been-revealed-using-dna-evidence-9717036.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

1921年-1922年俄罗斯大饥荒，因粮食不足，出现了大量人相食事件。<ref>{{Citation|url=https://www.icrc.org/fr/doc/resources/documents/misc/5qkjlh.htm|title=Secours en temps de paix - la famine en Russie - CICR|language=fr|last=Francis Haller|date=12 August 2003|journal=[[Le_Temps|Le Temps]]|publisher=published by [[ICRC|ICRC]]|access-date=14 March 2019|archivedate=2019-05-13|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190513024910/https://www.icrc.org/fr/doc/resources/documents/misc/5qkjlh.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>
==第二次世界大战==
有目击者描述了1941-1944年列宁格勒围城期间的食人现象。<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://observer.guardian.co.uk/life/story/0,6903,605454,00.html |title=Orchestral manoeuvres (part one) |date=November 25, 2001 |access-date=July 27, 2007 |work=The Guardian |location=London |first=Ed |last=Vulliamy |archive-date=2007-11-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071109205831/http://observer.guardian.co.uk/life/story/0,6903,605454,00.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

1943年1月和2月，德国士兵在[[斯大林格勒战役|斯大林格勒战役]]投降后，大约10万名德国士兵被俘虏。几乎所有这些人都被送往[[西伯利亚|西伯利亚]]或中亚的战俘营，在那里，由于长期吃不饱，许多战俘开始出现了人相食行为。<ref>{{cite book|author=Beevor, Antony|title=Stalingrad: The Fateful Siege|url=https://archive.org/details/stalingrad00beev|publisher=Penguin Books|date= 1999}}</ref>1942年11月，苏芬战争时期也出现了人相食现象。<ref name="#1">{{cite book|last1=Schindley|first1=Wanda |last2= Makara|first2=Petar |title=Jasenovac: proceedings of the First International Conference and Exhibit on the Jasenovac Concentration Camps, October 29-31, 1997, Kingsborough Community College of the City University of New York|date=2005|publisher=Dallas Pub.|isbn=9780912011646|page=149}}</ref><ref name="Jacobs">{{cite book|last=Jacobs|first=Steven L.|author-link=Steven L. Jacobs|title = Confronting Genocide: Judaism, Christianity, Islam|url=https://archive.org/details/confrontinggenoc00jaco|year=2009|publisher=Lexington Books|isbn=9780739135891|page=[https://archive.org/details/confrontinggenoc00jaco/page/n179 160]}}</ref>在纳粹德国设立的克罗地亚独立国集中营中也发生了大量人相食事件。<ref name="#1"/><ref name="Jacobs">{{cite book|last=Jacobs|first=Steven L.|author-link=Steven L. Jacobs|title = Confronting Genocide: Judaism, Christianity, Islam|url=https://archive.org/details/confrontinggenoc00jaco|year=2009|publisher=Lexington Books|isbn=9780739135891|page=[https://archive.org/details/confrontinggenoc00jaco/page/n179 160]}}</ref>
